HEADWORD: Deflagrable
<hw>De*fla"gra*ble</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Deflagrate</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Burning with a
sudden and sparkling combustion, as niter; hence, slightly explosive;
liable to snap and crackle when heated, as salt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deflagrate</ent>⟦br⟧
